content: Created a `pyproject.toml` that defines the package metadata, pins core dependencies (`numpy`, `matplotlib`), and registers the deterministic console script entrypoint `deterministic-runner = deterministic_runner.cli:main`.

output.code:
from pathlib import Path
import json

target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('pyproject.toml')
target_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

chunks = [
"""[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=68", "wheel"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta"

[project]
name = "deterministic-runner"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "Deterministic CLI entrypoint that writes fixed outputs and captures runtime metadata."
readme = "README.md"
requires-python = ">=3.9"
license = {text = "MIT"}
authors = [{name = "Generated Library"}]
keywords = ["deterministic", "reproducible", "cli"]
classifiers = [
  "Programming Language :: Python :: 3",
  "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License",
  "Operating System :: OS Independent",
]

dependencies = [
  "numpy>=1.22",
  "matplotlib>=3.6",
]

[project.urls]
Homepage = "https://example.invalid/deterministic-runner"
Repository = "https://example.invalid/deterministic-runner"

[project.scripts]
deterministic-runner = "deterministic_runner.cli:main"

[tool.setuptools]
package-dir = {"" = "src"}

[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
where = ["src"]
"""]

final_text = '\n'.join(block.strip('\n') for block in chunks).strip() + '\n'
target_path.write_text(final_text, encoding='utf-8')

print('FILE_WRITTEN:pyproject.toml')
print('DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file())))
